doc.after: Micronesians settled the Marshall Islands in the 2nd millennium BC but little is known of its early history People traveled by canoe between islands using traditional stick charts 3  Spanish explorer Alonso de Salazar was the first European to see the islands in 1526 commanding the ship Santa Maria de la Victoria the only surviving vessel of the Loa sa Expedition On August 21 he sighted an island probably Taongi at 14 N that he named San Bartolome 4
